cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper explores user behaviour on a social network platform (Tinder). 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses the strategies employed by men and women in using the app, which is related to user experience and interaction with technology. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper touches on societal implications of mobile dating apps. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on the technical aspects of the app, but rather on user behaviour. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also less likely as the paper does not involve natural language processing or language-related tasks.
